{
  "texts": [
    "The input is sent to the 1D array through the WLs, and the output is collected at the BL.",
    "Due to the single path for current flow in the BL, there is no issue of sneak path leakage current in such an array.",
    "Additionally, by applying a voltage to the WLs and grounding the BL, cross-talk issues can be addressed as each WL controls only one device.",
    "Consequently, the 1D memristor array is commonly used for basic computing concept verification, as it avoids uncertainties that may arise in large-scale arrays.",
    "For example, Xie et al."
  ]
}